Set Up a Cloud Storage Solution: Implement a cloud storage solution using S3 (AWS), Blob Storage (Azure), or Cloud Storage (GCP). Set up a content delivery network (CDN) and ensure the data is secure and accessible with proper permissions. 

Set up a Cloud Storage solution and CDN  using AWS S3 and Cloud Front(CDN). 

I created an s3 bucket to store profile images for the blog site app in question 1, I then enabled  CDN to deliver these images via Cloud Front CDN. 

For the s3 bucket, I created an IAM user and assigned roles to create, list

IAM User with bucket access permissions.

Cloud Front Permissions to access s3 Bucket
```
{  
        "Version": "2008-10-17",  
        "Id": "PolicyForCloudFrontPrivateContent",  
        "Statement": \[  
            {  
                "Sid": "AllowCloudFrontServicePrincipal",  
                "Effect": "Allow",  
                "Principal": {  
                    "Service": "cloudfront.amazonaws.com"  
                },  
                "Action": "s3:GetObject",  
                "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::blog-msc-kafuuma/\*",  
                "Condition": {  
                    "StringEquals": {  
                      "AWS:SourceArn": "arn:aws:cloudfront::691454643160:distribution/E3CG76DA56TW9R"  
                    }  
                }  
            }  
        \]  
      }
```
